# ASS-ADE — MCP Tool Reference

ASS-ADE is connected as an MCP server. It exposes developer-shell tools for
codebase analysis, blueprint generation, compliance checking, certification,
and agentic workflows.

## CLI tools (local, no API key required)

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `doctor` | Environment diagnostics — config, Python version, toolchain |
| `recon` | Parallel codebase reconnaissance — structure, deps, quality signals |
| `eco_scan` | Monadic compliance scan — tier violations, circular deps, coverage |
| `lint` | Ruff linting with optional auto-fix |
| `certify` | SHA-256 tamper-evident certificate for the current repo state |
| `design` | Enhancement blueprint — tier-annotated plan with gap analysis |
| `rebuild` | Rebuild into 5-tier monadic structure with certificate output |

## IDE tools (file system, read/write/edit)

`read_file`, `write_file`, `edit_file`, `undo_edit`, `run_command`,
`list_directory`, `search_files`, `grep_search`

## Workflow tools

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `phase0_recon` | Never-Code-Blind gate — require source targets before coding |
| `context_pack` | Build a compact task context packet from recon + file excerpts |
| `context_memory_store` | Store text into local vector memory |
| `context_memory_query` | Query local vector memory |
| `map_terrain` | MAP = TERRAIN capability gate — verify required assets exist |
| `trust_gate` | Multi-step agent trust gate (identity, sybil, trust, reputation) |
| `certify_output` | Certify agent output via hallucination oracle + ethics checks |
| `safe_execute` | Execute a tool inside trust + ethics pre-flight |
| `ask_agent` | Send a task through the full ASS-ADE agent loop |

## A2A tools

`a2a_validate`, `a2a_negotiate`

## Prompt tools

`prompt_hash`, `prompt_validate`, `prompt_section`, `prompt_diff`, `prompt_propose`

## Usage notes

- All local tools run offline — no API key required.
- `trust_gate`, `certify_output`, and `safe_execute` require a hybrid/premium
  profile with a Nexus API key (`AAAA_NEXUS_API_KEY` env var).
- `rebuild` writes a versioned output folder — it does not overwrite the source.
- `eco_scan` scores conformance 0–100; below 60 exits with code 1.
